values:
For the first time in my life, i called the cops for a noise violation.

This is after I went upstairs at 5:20 and asked&nbsp;my 30-something neighbor&nbsp;to keep the noise down, and fell down the stairs, and talked to alicia, and then my parents, left about 4 voicemails with my landlord (a chicago cop, ironically) and watched the first 45 min of almost famous.&nbsp; at 7:15 the noise was much louder than a dull roar -- it seemed the party was gaining momentum rather than slowing down.&nbsp; So i called and non-anonymously placed a noise violation complaint.&nbsp; i even went outside (again) to prop open the gate so the cops could get in.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Sweet victory was mine, as the cops banged on the door, and I heard the music go from about a 50 on a scale of 1-10 to a 2 before my neighbor opened the door.&nbsp; Muffled&nbsp;speech was&nbsp;exchanged, and things settled down.

I guess it was a premature victory, however, because 10 minutes later the noise level was the same.&nbsp; i waited, hoping that the noise would die down, as it was then 7:45.&nbsp; Of course, this has to be the worst day ever.&nbsp; So i called my landlord, left another angry message. &nbsp;right when I hung up, my phone rang.&nbsp; Landlord.&nbsp;&nbsp;

The moral of the story is, I no longer feel like an asshole when the noise has been persistent for 3 hrs and I call the cops.&nbsp; SO THERE.


Sleep, however, is a lost cause.&nbsp; So I'm eating breakfast, and going to go do laundry in a few minutes.&nbsp; and in a little while, when everything gets quiet, i am going to go upstairs and wake everybody up:)
